<h2><span class="mw-headline" id="Release_details">Release details</span><span class="mw-editsection"><span class="mw-editsection-bracket">[</span><a href="/w/index.php?title=Caste:_The_Origins_of_Our_Discontents&amp;action=edit&amp;section=8" title="Edit section: Release details"><span>edit</span></a><span class="mw-editsection-bracket">]</span></span></h2>
<p>The book became a number one <a href="/wiki/The_New_York_Times_Best_Seller_list" title="The New York Times Best Seller list"><i>New York Times</i> nonfiction best-seller</a> in early November 2020<sup id="cite_ref-NYTBS1November2020_52-0" class="reference"><a href="#cite_note-NYTBS1November2020-52">&#91;52&#93;</a></sup> and, as of the September 26, 2021, issue, had spent 58 weeks on The Times nonfiction best sellers list.<sup id="cite_ref-53" class="reference"><a href="#cite_note-53">&#91;53&#93;</a></sup> It is also a <i><a href="/wiki/USA_Today" title="USA Today">USA Today</a></i> Best Seller, having debuted on August 13, 2020, the book peaked at number three and has spent 21 weeks on the list as of January 5, 2021.<sup id="cite_ref-54" class="reference"><a href="#cite_note-54">&#91;54&#93;</a></sup> According to <i><a href="/wiki/Publishers_Weekly" title="Publishers Weekly">Publishers Weekly</a></i>, the book had sold over half a million copies by the close of 2020.<sup id="cite_ref-55" class="reference"><a href="#cite_note-55">&#91;55&#93;</a></sup>
</p>
<ul><li>Hardcover: <link rel="mw-deduplicated-inline-style" href="mw-data:TemplateStyles:r1215172403"><cite id="CITEREFWilkerson2020" class="citation book cs1">Wilkerson, Isabel (4 August 2020). <i>Caste: The Origins of Our Discontents</i>. New York: Random House. <a href="/wiki/ISBN_(identifier)" class="mw-redirect" title="ISBN (identifier)">ISBN</a>&#160;<a href="/wiki/Special:BookSources/978-0-593-23025-1" title="Special:BookSources/978-0-593-23025-1"><bdi>978-0-593-23025-1</bdi></a>. <a href="/wiki/OCLC_(identifier)" class="mw-redirect" title="OCLC (identifier)">OCLC</a>&#160;<a rel="nofollow" class="external text" href="https://www.worldcat.org/oclc/1147928120">1147928120</a>.</cite><span title="ctx_ver=Z39.88-2004&amp;rft_val_fmt=info%3Aofi%2Ffmt%3Akev%3Amtx%3Abook&amp;rft.genre=book&amp;rft.btitle=Caste%3A+The+Origins+of+Our+Discontents&amp;rft.place=New+York&amp;rft.pub=Random+House&amp;rft.date=2020-08-04&amp;rft_id=info%3Aoclcnum%2F1147928120&amp;rft.isbn=978-0-593-23025-1&amp;rft.aulast=Wilkerson&amp;rft.aufirst=Isabel&amp;rfr_id=info%3Asid%2Fen.wikipedia.org%3ACaste%3A+The+Origins+of+Our+Discontents" class="Z3988"></span> (496 pp.)</li>
<li>Digital: <link rel="mw-deduplicated-inline-style" href="mw-data:TemplateStyles:r1215172403"><cite id="CITEREFWilkerson2020" class="citation book cs1">Wilkerson, Isabel (4 August 2020). <i>Caste: The Origins of Our Discontents</i>. New York: Random House. <a href="/wiki/ISBN_(identifier)" class="mw-redirect" title="ISBN (identifier)">ISBN</a>&#160;<a href="/wiki/Special:BookSources/978-0-593-23026-8" title="Special:BookSources/978-0-593-23026-8"><bdi>978-0-593-23026-8</bdi></a>. <a href="/wiki/OCLC_(identifier)" class="mw-redirect" title="OCLC (identifier)">OCLC</a>&#160;<a rel="nofollow" class="external text" href="https://www.worldcat.org/oclc/1147928120">1147928120</a>.</cite><span title="ctx_ver=Z39.88-2004&amp;rft_val_fmt=info%3Aofi%2Ffmt%3Akev%3Amtx%3Abook&amp;rft.genre=book&amp;rft.btitle=Caste%3A+The+Origins+of+Our+Discontents&amp;rft.place=New+York&amp;rft.pub=Random+House&amp;rft.date=2020-08-04&amp;rft_id=info%3Aoclcnum%2F1147928120&amp;rft.isbn=978-0-593-23026-8&amp;rft.aulast=Wilkerson&amp;rft.aufirst=Isabel&amp;rfr_id=info%3Asid%2Fen.wikipedia.org%3ACaste%3A+The+Origins+of+Our+Discontents" class="Z3988"></span> (496 pp.)</li>
<li>Audiobook (CD): <link rel="mw-deduplicated-inline-style" href="mw-data:TemplateStyles:r1215172403"><cite id="CITEREFWilkerson2020" class="citation cs2">Wilkerson, Isabel (18 August 2020), <i>Caste: The Origins of Our Discontents</i>, <a href="/wiki/Robin_Miles" title="Robin Miles">Miles, Robin</a>, New York: Random House Audio, <a href="/wiki/ISBN_(identifier)" class="mw-redirect" title="ISBN (identifier)">ISBN</a>&#160;<a href="/wiki/Special:BookSources/978-0-593-39669-8" title="Special:BookSources/978-0-593-39669-8"><bdi>978-0-593-39669-8</bdi></a>, <a href="/wiki/OCLC_(identifier)" class="mw-redirect" title="OCLC (identifier)">OCLC</a>&#160;<a rel="nofollow" class="external text" href="https://www.worldcat.org/oclc/1176245188">1176245188</a></cite><span title="ctx_ver=Z39.88-2004&amp;rft_val_fmt=info%3Aofi%2Ffmt%3Akev%3Amtx%3Abook&amp;rft.genre=book&amp;rft.btitle=Caste%3A+The+Origins+of+Our+Discontents&amp;rft.place=New+York&amp;rft.pub=Random+House+Audio&amp;rft.date=2020-08-18&amp;rft_id=info%3Aoclcnum%2F1176245188&amp;rft.isbn=978-0-593-39669-8&amp;rft.aulast=Wilkerson&amp;rft.aufirst=Isabel&amp;rfr_id=info%3Asid%2Fen.wikipedia.org%3ACaste%3A+The+Origins+of+Our+Discontents" class="Z3988"></span> (870 minutes)</li>
<li>Audiobook (MP3): <link rel="mw-deduplicated-inline-style" href="mw-data:TemplateStyles:r1215172403"><cite id="CITEREFWilkerson,_Isabel2020" class="citation cs2">Wilkerson, Isabel (4 August 2020), <i>Caste: The Origins of Our Discontents</i>, <a href="/wiki/Robin_Miles" title="Robin Miles">Miles, Robin</a>, New York: Random House Audio, <a href="/wiki/ISBN_(identifier)" class="mw-redirect" title="ISBN (identifier)">ISBN</a>&#160;<a href="/wiki/Special:BookSources/978-0-593-33980-0" title="Special:BookSources/978-0-593-33980-0"><bdi>978-0-593-33980-0</bdi></a>, <a href="/wiki/OCLC_(identifier)" class="mw-redirect" title="OCLC (identifier)">OCLC</a>&#160;<a rel="nofollow" class="external text" href="https://www.worldcat.org/oclc/1182631574">1182631574</a></cite><span title="ctx_ver=Z39.88-2004&amp;rft_val_fmt=info%3Aofi%2Ffmt%3Akev%3Amtx%3Abook&amp;rft.genre=book&amp;rft.btitle=Caste%3A+The+Origins+of+Our+Discontents&amp;rft.place=New+York&amp;rft.pub=Random+House+Audio&amp;rft.date=2020-08-04&amp;rft_id=info%3Aoclcnum%2F1182631574&amp;rft.isbn=978-0-593-33980-0&amp;rft.au=Wilkerson%2C+Isabel&amp;rfr_id=info%3Asid%2Fen.wikipedia.org%3ACaste%3A+The+Origins+of+Our+Discontents" class="Z3988"></span> (867 minutes)</li>
<li>Paperback: <link rel="mw-deduplicated-inline-style" href="mw-data:TemplateStyles:r1215172403"><cite class="citation book cs1"><i>Caste: the origins of our discontents</i>. Random House trade paperback. 14 February 2023. <a href="/wiki/ISBN_(identifier)" class="mw-redirect" title="ISBN (identifier)">ISBN</a>&#160;<a href="/wiki/Special:BookSources/9780593230275" title="Special:BookSources/9780593230275"><bdi>9780593230275</bdi></a>. <a href="/wiki/OCLC_(identifier)" class="mw-redirect" title="OCLC (identifier)">OCLC</a>&#160;<a rel="nofollow" class="external text" href="https://www.worldcat.org/oclc/1369859133">1369859133</a>.</cite><span title="ctx_ver=Z39.88-2004&amp;rft_val_fmt=info%3Aofi%2Ffmt%3Akev%3Amtx%3Abook&amp;rft.genre=book&amp;rft.btitle=Caste%3A+the+origins+of+our+discontents&amp;rft.pub=Random+House+trade+paperback&amp;rft.date=2023-02-14&amp;rft_id=info%3Aoclcnum%2F1369859133&amp;rft.isbn=9780593230275&amp;rfr_id=info%3Asid%2Fen.wikipedia.org%3ACaste%3A+The+Origins+of+Our+Discontents" class="Z3988"></span></li></ul>
<p>The book is published in the UK under the title <i>Caste: The Lies That Divide Us</i>.<sup id="cite_ref-56" class="reference"><a href="#cite_note-56">&#91;56&#93;</a></sup>
</p>
